title: fingertips
lyrics:
when i look back, tracing fingertips over plastic bags<c> thinking, i wish i could extrapolate somesmallintention<c> or maybe justget your attention for a minuteor two
<c> will i die? or will i get to that tenyear mark?<c> where i beat the extinction of telomeres?<c> and if i do, will you be there with me, father, sister, brother?

title: ride monologue
lyrics:
i was in the winter of my life<c> and the men i met along the road were my only summer<c> at night i fell asleep with visions of myself dancing and laughing and crying with them<c> three years down the line of being on an endless world tour and my memories of them were the only things that sustained me<c> and my only real happy times<c> i was a singer<c> not a very popular one<c> i once had dreams of becoming a beautiful poet<c> but upon an unfortunate series of events saw those dreams dashed and divided like a million stars in the night sky<c> that i wished on over and over again, sparkling and broken<c> but i didnt really mind because i knew that it takes getting everything you ever wanted and then losing it to know what true freedom is<c> when the people i used to know found out what i had been doing how i had been living, they asked me why, but theres no use in talking to people who have a home<c> they have no idea what its like to seek safety in other people<c> for home to be wherever you lie your head<c> i was always an unusual girl<c> my mother told me that i had a chameleon soul<c> no moral compass pointing due north<c> no fixed personality<c> just an inner indecisiveness that was as wide and as wavering as the ocean<c> and if i said i didnt plan for it to turn out this way id be lying<c> because i was born to be the other woman<c> who belonged to no one<c> who belonged to everyone<c> who had nothing<c> who wanted everything<c> with a fire for every experience and an obsession for freedom that terrified me to the point that i couldnt even talk about it<c> and pushed me to a nomadic point of madness that both dazzled and dizzied me
<c> every night i used to pray that id find my people<c> and finally i did<c> on the open road<c> we had nothing to lose, nothing to gain, nothing we desired anymore<c> except to make our lives into a work of art<c> live fast<c> die young<c> be wild<c> and have fun<c> i believe in the country america used to be<c> i believe in the person i want to become<c> i believe in the freedom of the open road<c> and my motto is the same as ever
i believe in the kindness of strangers<c> and when im at war with myself<c> i ride<c> i just ride<c> who are you?<c> are you in touch with all of your darkest fantasies?<c> have you created a life for yourself where you can experience them?<c> i have<c> i am fucking crazy<c> but i am free
